{"author":{"id":"6c02eaf2589fb23ac29485c7ab6ab1f261da2854488931d815ccfe49ff0ce44a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1542049481,"nonce":"WbYWBFQrHqebB/clI3jbVoRaL/k=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzNzk5Mzg5MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/72#issuecomment-437993890"},"message":"Eh, \"priority\" and/or \"severity\" are quite common for \"real\" bug trackers, e.g. [bugzilla](https://www.bugzilla.org/) or [mantis](http://www.mantisbt.org/). Priority usually expresses the importance of getting a bug fixes/an issue closed, often from the maintainer's point of view. Severity expresses the impact of a bug/issue (e.g. is it only inconvenient, does the application crash or does it corrupt data). Both are often used for sorting issues and deciding what to tackle next.\n\nOT: there are alternatives to maintainer-/user-set priority, e.g. \"[user pain](http://www.lostgarden.com/2008/05/improving-bug-triage-with-user-pain.html)\".","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1542049544,"nonce":"462wlHNSTWH7jy4jkb34bM9kQe8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDE1MDc0OTQ4MA=="},"target":"ebaee8c8ec62682219cd8768185f77faeead35abd7c9e158d5004aba0070c142","message":"Er, \"priority\" and/or \"severity\" are quite common for \"real\" bug trackers, e.g. [bugzilla](https://www.bugzilla.org/) or [mantis](http://www.mantisbt.org/). Priority usually expresses the importance of getting a bug fixes/an issue closed, often from the maintainer's point of view. Severity expresses the impact of a bug/issue (e.g. is it only inconvenient, does the application crash or does it corrupt data). Both are often used for sorting issues and deciding what to tackle next.\n\nOT: there are alternatives to maintainer-/user-set priority, e.g. \"[user pain](http://www.lostgarden.com/2008/05/improving-bug-triage-with-user-pain.html)\".","files":null}]}